name: gyudon
source: https://www.andy-cooks.com/blogs/recipes/gyudon-japanese-beef-and-rice-bowl
notes: |
  Andy Cooks' gyudon — Japanese stewed beef & onion bowl (video: https://youtu.be/M-PuGg7Ek-w).
  Serve over rice (cook separately in a rice cooker). Poaching the beef gently keeps it tender —
  no dry heat to toughen the fibres.
  Freeze the beef 20-30 mins before slicing for cleaner, thinner cuts; slice against the grain.
  Beef & broth keep separately up to 2 days; reheat gently with a splash of water.
ingredients:
  - item: beef
    mass: 180
    basis: true
    note: ribeye is ideal; steak offcuts or supermarket stir-fry beef also work. sliced paper-thin against the grain; ~150-220g per person
  - item: brown onion
    qty: 1
    unit: ea
    note: finely sliced; lots — it cooks down
  - item: water
    mass: 100
  - item: dashi powder
    qty: 0.5
    unit: tsp
    note: instant; Andy Cooks' site uses 1 tsp
  - item: soy sauce
    qty: 1
    unit: tbsp
    note: light
  - item: mirin
    qty: 1
    unit: tbsp
  - item: sake
    qty: 0.5
    unit: tbsp
  - item: garlic
    qty: 1
    unit: clove
    note: finely grated
  - item: ginger
    note: ½ thumb-size piece, finely grated
  - item: egg
    qty: 1
    unit: ea
    note: soft-boiled
  - item: spring onions
    qty: 2
    unit: ea
    note: whites & greens separated
  - item: rice
    note: 1 cup steamed Japanese short-grain
  - pink pickled ginger
  - sesame seeds
steps:
  - soft-boil an egg for exactly 6 mins, shock in ice water 1-2 mins, then peel and set aside
  - bring water to a simmer and whisk in dashi powder, soy sauce, mirin and sake
  - grate in garlic and ginger, keep at a very gentle simmer (no salt needed — dashi has it)
  - add sliced onion and cook over low-medium heat for 4-5 mins until soft and translucent
  - add the paper-thin beef in a single layer and poach 2-3 mins until just cooked; add a splash of water if dry
  - slice the spring onion whites on an angle and fold through the beef; taste and adjust salt, then heat off
  - serve over rice, ladling over plenty of broth
  - top with the halved soft-boiled egg, pink pickled ginger, spring onion greens and sesame seeds
